# Robot geometry

The Go2 has four legs, each with hip-abduction, thigh, and calf joints. For these tasks, hip abduction stays at zero, so each leg moves only in its sagittal (forward-back + up-down) plane.

In the body frame (origin at the center of the trunk):

- Front-left (FL)  hip at ( 0.1934,  0.0465, 0) m
- Front-right (FR) hip at ( 0.1934, -0.0465, 0) m
- Rear-left  (RL)  hip at (-0.1934,  0.0465, 0) m
- Rear-right (RR)  hip at (-0.1934, -0.0465, 0) m

Each leg has thigh length L1 = 0.213 m and calf length L2 = 0.213 m, so max foot-to-hip distance is 0.426 m.

The robot starts each iteration at its home standing pose: base height ≈ 0.27 m, level body, all four feet directly under their hips at foot_z ≈ -0.27 m.